To increase EBS volume

Step 1: Modify Volume in AWS Console
  Go to EC2 > Volumes (left sidebar under "Elastic Block Store").
  Find the volume attached to your instance (check instance ID).
  Select it → Actions > Modify Volume
  Set size to 24 GiB → Modify → Confirm.
  AWS will start the modification (takes a few seconds to minutes).

Step 2: Resize Filesystem on EC2
  SSH into your instance, then run:
    lsblk

    Find your device name (likely /dev/xvda1 or /dev/nvme0n1p1 depending on AMI type). Now extend the filesystem:

  Ubuntu (ext4 default):
    sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1
    sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1

  Ubuntu (if using nvme):
    sudo growpart /dev/nvme0n1 1
    sudo resize2fs /dev/nvme0n1p1

Step 3: Verify
  df -h


